# Mirror block modules

Blocks under `src/mirror-poll/`, `src/mirror-sync/`, and `src/mirror-merge/` are
self-contained pipeline stages.

## Imports

Cross-module imports are limited to:

- `../git/*` -- git subprocess helpers and `Logger`
- `../types/*` -- shared types (e.g. `mirror-sync-config`, `replay-entry`)

Also allowed:

- Node.js built-ins
- Relative imports within the same block (`./config.ts`, `./queue.ts`, ...)

## Do not import

- `../lib/*`, `../cli/*`, or other blocks (`../mirror-sync/*`, etc.)

Shared helpers needed by a block belong in that block (or in `src/git/` /
`src/types/` if truly shared). Do not pull Block 1 `repos.ts` or other lib code
into mirror blocks.

Orchestration that wires blocks together lives in `src/lib/` or `src/cli/`, not
inside mirror block modules.
